    "## Data Splitting Strategy\n",
    "\n",
    "### Dataset analysis informing split strategy\n",
    "From data inspection (Cell 6):\n",
    "- 1,800 independent campaign-level observations — no temporal dependency\n",
    "- Revenue is right-skewed: 75th percentile at $38,963 vs max $295,028\n",
    "- Campaigns span 3 platforms, 7 countries, 5 industries, 4 campaign types\n",
    "- No sensor IDs, location clusters, or time dependencies between rows\n",
    "- Conclusion: random split with stratification on revenue is appropriate\n",
    "\n",
    "### Strategy chosen: Random split with stratification\n",
    "\n",
    "**Rationale:**\n",
    "The Global Ads Performance dataset contains 1,800 independent campaign-level \n",
    "observations. Each campaign row is independent. A TikTok campaign in the UAE has \n",
    "no temporal or structural dependency on a Google Ads campaign in Canada. \n",
    "This rules out temporal and grouped splitting strategies.\n",
    "\n",
    "Stratification is applied because revenue (our target variable) is right-skewed, \n",
    "with most campaigns earning under $38,963, but some earning up to $295,028. \n",
    "Stratification bins the revenue distribution into 5 equal-frequency groups to \n",
    "ensure both train and test sets proportionally represent low, medium, and \n",
    "high-revenue campaigns.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Split parameters:**\n",
    "- Test size: 20% (360 rows for testing, 1,440 rows for training)\n",
    "- Random state: 42 (ensures reproducibility)\n",
    "- Stratification: 5 quantile bins on revenue\n",
    "\n",
    "**Leakage prevention:**\n",
    "- ROAS excluded — derived from revenue (revenue / ad_spend)\n",
    "- CPA excluded — derived from conversions and ad_spend\n",
    "- Raw date column excluded — replaced by month and quarter\n",
    "- StandardScaler will be fit on the training set only in the next cell\n",
    "\n",
    "### Reproducibility notes\n",
    "- random_state=42 ensures an identical split on every run\n",
    "- pd.qcut with q=5 creates equal-frequency revenue bins\n",
    "- drop_first=True in get_dummies prevents multicollinearity\n",
    "- All four output files saved with self-explanatory names"
   ]
